By Chibuike
Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – Former President, Dr. Goodluck Jonathan, on Tuesday congratulated Muslims on the celebration of Eid-el-Fitr. Goodluck while wishing Eid Mubarak to the Muslim Ummah, prayed
Allah to grant Nigerians their heart desires according to His eternal will.
This is also as he prayed for this season to ushers Nigerians into a season of
peace, love and joy. The former president gave the message when he took to his twitter handle and
said: “Eid Mubarak to the Muslim
Ummah, may this season usher into our homes peace, love and joy. “May Allah
grant us our heart desires according to His eternal will. Happy Celebrations. –
GEJ”. Recall that Muslims all over the world are celebrating
Eid-el-fitri today.